<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-07-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-07-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="715" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d715">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Merry</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">San
                                        Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-07-22"><hi rend="italic">July 22,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Merry states that he has received a telegram from the President of
                            Honduras requesting him to present to the President of the United States
                            the gratitude of the Government and people of Honduras for his friendly
                            and efficient mediation in obtaining peace tween Guatemala, Salvador,
                            and Honduras.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>